1	\paragraph{2015 B--1 \textnormal{[\texttt{differentiability}]}}
2	Let $f$ be a three times differentiable function (defined on $\mathbb{R}$ and real-valued) such that $f$ has at least five distinct real zeros. Prove that $f + 6f' + 12f'' + 8f'''$ has at least two distinct real zeros.
